Madhya Pradesh
Sep 01, 2014
Murder
Description:
			A local court awarded a life sentence to a youth today, for murdering his wife by setting her on fire after a dispute.

The sentence was awarded by Additional Session Judge S K Shrivastava to Sunil Badoudia (26) under Section 302 of the Indian Penal Code and besides a fine of Rs 1000.

The court convicted Badoudia for killing his 20-year- old wife Varsha in the Balda Colony area, Additional Government Advocate (AGP) Mohanlal Bagora said.

Badoudia set his wife afire by pouring kerosene over her after a dispute.

She succumbed to her burn injuries on June 29, 2011.


